<br>
Due to the demands of all my other chars...uhhgg, I didn't have a lot of money to spend on my finished Merc (will he ever be) so, for quick weapons I took him and my Pally down to Dart to kill a few named Giants and pick up a couple of Featherlite Granite Hammers. I use the procc as well as the weapon and am always getting offers for em. Have you tried these cheap (free) weapons and if so, what do you think?<br>
<br>
I also wonder what you think of the styles we (crush) Mercs have available? I really like Crush but dont consider myself an expert. eg. I try to use as many DW styles as possible, but cant seem to remove Concussion from my Qbar. It still scales well in damage as well as the snare effect. You can laugh, but I still find that general style so damn useful.<br>
<br>
I always keep two reactive and two positional stles available; Reflection/ Hypnotic reaction, and Flank/ Shadows positional. <br>
<br>
Beyond and activation proccs, thats about it generally although I sometimes use Dual, not so impressed...<br>
<br>
Any ideas you can give me I'd appreciate....<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=oosubparoo>oO Subpar Oo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#000000>(4/10/03 4:17:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=50.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re: Hey Nirala! question plz..</span><hr size=1> I know I'm not Nirala, and I'm not a crush merc, so dunno how useful this will be for ya, but for non-frontal positional, I like shadow's edge (or Pierce in my case, since I'm thrust and prefer the thrust back-style over the DW back-style)...probably use it just as much as any other styles because casters and healers always run away, so it's nice to have a handy backstyle available...not sure if crush has something better though? I know you guys have an anytime-stun chain. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Must be useful chasing down casters and healers. Anywho, just my two cents..<br>
